Task: Loan Default Risk Prediction (Advanced Modeling)
Objective: Predict the probability of loan default by integrating multi-table relational data from various financial bureaus.

Key Skills: XGBoost, Multi-table Data Merging, Class Imbalance Handling.

Technical Challenges Overcome: * Resolved complex KeyError issues by resetting indices during the aggregation of bureau.csv.

Fixed strict XGBoost TypeError constraints by enforcing float32 numeric casting across all encoded categorical features.

Addressed class imbalance (Target=1 being rare) by utilizing scale_pos_weight to improve recall.

Outcome: A high-performance gradient boosting model capable of assessing applicant risk across multiple financial dimensions, specifically highlighting the importance of external credit scores.
